.TH "mesh_path_fix_nexthop" 9 "mesh_path_fix_nexthop" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mesh_path_fix_nexthop \- force a specific next hop for a mesh path
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" mesh_path_fix_nexthop
.BI "(struct mesh_path *mpath "  ","
.BI "struct sta_info *next_hop "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mpath" 12
the mesh path to modify
.IP "next_hop" 12
the next hop to force
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Locking: this function must be called holding mpath->state_lock
